1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:32,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,662
-Hey, man!
-Please!

3
00:00:37,746 --> 00:00:39,497
Is this really the only CCTV
that you can hack?

4
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:40,457
Why, what happened?

5
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:42,208
-He already had Mikoy kidnapped.
-Huh?

6
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:45,170
What the hell are you doing?
In Tagalog… What are you doing?

7
00:00:46,212 --> 00:00:47,464
I’m sorry.

8
00:00:47,547 --> 00:00:50,884
Why didn't you tell me
that you're from a rich family?

9
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:54,429
Does something have to change
just because my status in life is higher?

10
00:00:54,512 --> 00:00:56,431
It's just that I met a girl.

11
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:58,808
She’s the daughter of one

12
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:01,311
of the richest families
here in Prague. That level!

13
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:03,688
I want to open my heart for you.

14
00:01:03,772 --> 00:01:05,815
I’m ready to make it work.

15
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:11,196
…Mr. Mikoy D. Pinagpala.

16
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:16,951
So, tomorrow you'll go
straight to the villa?

17
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:19,662
Just give Mom and Dad a chance.

18
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:21,915
They just want to meet you.

19
00:01:31,382 --> 00:01:32,258
All right.

20
00:01:34,385 --> 00:01:35,595
let's just meet tomorrow?

21
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:37,806
Okay.

22
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:39,432
All right. Get in now.

23
00:01:40,016 --> 00:01:41,226
Aren't you riding with me?

24
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:42,393
I can drop you off.

25
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:45,480
No, it's okay. I’m fine. I'll just walk.

26
00:01:45,563 --> 00:01:47,315
My place is just nearby, anyway.

27
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:49,484
Okay.

28
00:01:50,318 --> 00:01:52,445
Just avoid Nerudova.

29
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:55,323
Huh? Why?

30
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:56,991
That's my shortcut.

31
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,452
And besides,

32
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:02,247
Prague is a very safe city. Right?

33
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:06,835
But tonight…

34
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:09,337
there's no moon.

35
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:22,934
Why are you getting nervous?

36
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:25,687
I'm not! Not at all.

37
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:29,023
Seriously, you’re like your father.

38
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:31,401
All right, get in now.

39
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:32,360
Okay.

40
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:35,697
All right, see you!

41
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,714
I thought you were a ghost.

42
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:40,220
Now I know why Chiara fell for you.

43
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:41,554
Filipino?

44
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:50,605
And I'm afraid you need to come with me,

45
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:52,774
Mr. Mikoy D. Pinagpala.

46
00:03:56,277 --> 00:03:58,238
You’re crazy.

47
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,562
Oh… Who are you?

48
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:34,315
Just relax. Sit down.

49
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:03,136
Just call me "Sianong" for short.

50
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:05,638
To make it sound more friendly. Right?

51
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:07,682
Okay.

52
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,852
What do you need from me?

53
00:05:12,895 --> 00:05:15,898
Look, we’re not bad people.

54
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:18,735
The fact that you're not tied up
and free to go.

55
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:21,612
But we really need your help.

56
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:33,708
We know about
your relationship with Chiara.

57
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:36,294
And we want to use your unique situation

58
00:05:36,377 --> 00:05:39,088
because we're investigating
the Valtrovi’s.

59
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:43,718
Viktor Valtrovi.

60
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,389
Investigation?

61
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:50,349
For what?

62
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:10,119
In Tagalog… What are you doing?

63
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:24,092
This is a joke!

64
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,512
Sir Viktor is really playful, huh?

65
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:29,138
He's really good at pranks!

66
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:35,269
You're so crazy, Sir Viktor!

67
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:36,979
You always like joking with me!

68
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:42,318
Do you know, son,

69
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:44,821
a congressman was killed here?

70
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:48,157
He’s Partylist Congressman Salazar.

71
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:50,243
No history of corruption.

72
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:53,704
No campaign contributor
who’s a contractor.

73
00:06:54,705 --> 00:06:57,959
And the only "crime" of Celestino Salazar

74
00:06:58,042 --> 00:06:59,335
was that he started investigating

75
00:06:59,418 --> 00:07:02,088
all the criminal activities
of the Moraviano Syndicate,

76
00:07:02,171 --> 00:07:04,924
which is headed by Viktor Valtrovi.

77
00:07:06,342 --> 00:07:10,096
And we strongly believe
the order directly came from him

78
00:07:10,179 --> 00:07:11,764
to get Celestino killed.

79
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:16,060
Of course, he doesn’t want
everything he does in the Philippines

80
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,562
with his syndicate to be exposed.

81
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:20,815
I know it's hard to believe.

82
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:24,277
But this is not a joke!

83
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:26,446
This is serious, Mikoy!

84
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:30,450
That is why we're coming to you.

85
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:33,661
With your relationship with Chiara,

86
00:07:34,203 --> 00:07:36,998
we now have a way to get close to Viktor.

87
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:39,333
To gather evidence against him.

88
00:07:40,042 --> 00:07:42,336
And to build a case against him.

89
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:45,173
So he can pay for his crimes.

90
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:51,637
You are the only key
to bringing down the Moraviano.

91
00:07:51,721 --> 00:07:53,556
Do you think

92
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,475
I would believe you?

93
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,685
And if what you're saying is true,

94
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,771
Chiara has nothing to do
with her family’s mess.

95
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:02,940
She shouldn't be dragged into this.

96
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:07,361
But she’s using
her parents’ money and wealth.

97
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:09,906
So, it means she’s involved.

98
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:12,158
In short, she’s a nepo baby.

99
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:15,119
First of all, you kidnapped me.

100
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:18,080
Second, why should I believe you?

101
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,582
For all I know,

102
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:21,876
you might actually be the syndicate,

103
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:24,253
and all your stories are made up
just to ruin them.

104
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:29,091
If you're not bad people,

105
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,177
then can I leave now?

106
00:08:38,226 --> 00:08:39,477
Wait, you forgot something.

107
00:08:40,978 --> 00:08:43,022
Again?

108
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:31,070
I'm Special Agent Alexandria.

109
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:33,614
And we want to use your unique situation.

110
00:09:34,198 --> 00:09:35,283
We've been watching you.

111
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:36,951
Could you help us, Mr. Pinagpala?

112
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,130
What was that?

113
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,007
Was it a nightmare?

114
00:10:44,518 --> 00:10:47,188
He fell down the stairs. Dead!

115
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:30,439
Nice one!

116
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,074
His name is

117
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:42,701
-Don Vito.
-Vito!

118
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:45,121
Okay! We already know that one! Okay!

119
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:52,670
I don't even know why
I ended up liking him.

120
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:57,675
Yes. Actually, the stories
of Sir Viktor are funny.

121
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,145
-I will marry him!
-Hey!

122
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:16,986
Is it okay that I already
introduced you to Mom and Dad?

123
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:19,363
Isn’t it too fast?

124
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:21,949
Uhm, not really.

125
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:25,744
It's not a problem.
That's how it should be, right?

126
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:30,291
Well, they seem to like you.

127
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:33,002
But sometimes

128
00:12:33,752 --> 00:12:35,463
I don't understand them.

129
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:37,631
Yes, they're my parents,

130
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:40,426
but sometimes, it feels like
I don't know them.

131
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:45,681
What do you mean you don't know them?

132
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:49,477
Well, for example, you.

133
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:54,690
My mom and dad don't trust people easily.

134
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:58,068
But for some reason,

135
00:12:58,152 --> 00:13:00,237
you won them over immediately.

136
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:09,997
Are they really like that?

137
00:13:11,707 --> 00:13:14,001
They don't trust people easily?

138
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,964
It comes with the territory.

139
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:21,050
Given their status in life,

140
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:24,470
they have many enemies.

141
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,727
That's why they are very protective of me.

142
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:36,899
Because not everyone who approaches me

143
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,944
has good intentions.

144
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:41,171
Who's there?

145
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,508
What are you doing here?

146
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,094
I knew it. That wasn't a nightmare!

147
00:15:29,678 --> 00:15:31,305
You kidnapped me last night.

148
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:34,892
And now, you just walked
into my house without permission!

149
00:15:36,393 --> 00:15:37,978
Who knows?

150
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:40,439
You might even take
advantage of me while I'm asleep.

151
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:44,860
I apologize for our method.

152
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:48,364
But you must understand,

153
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:50,532
the Valtrovi are not simple enemies.

154
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:53,035
We have to move quietly.

155
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:55,955
Because if they sense
that we’re investigating them,

156
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:05,255
Do you still not believe us?

157
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:08,968
How am I supposed to believe you?

158
00:16:09,551 --> 00:16:11,720
You haven't even shown any evidence.

159
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:14,306
All you have are accusations and all talk.

160
00:16:18,268 --> 00:16:21,647
Help us to build a case
against the Moravianos.

161
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:25,609
So we can gather evidence
against Chiara's family.

162
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:28,028
You know what? Chiara is a good person.

163
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:33,033
She doesn't deserve
that just as our relationship is starting,

164
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:34,702
I'm already lying to her.

165
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:36,829
And honestly,

166
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:39,540
they're a little bit weird

167
00:16:39,623 --> 00:16:41,875
and a little sketchy, but…

168
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:44,920
they're actually kind people.

169
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:49,091
Because if we’re wrong,

170
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:53,262
and they really have nothing to do
with the Moravianos,

171
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:58,517
then there is nothing wrong
if you help us investigate them.

172
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,240
Think carefully about it, Mikoy.

173
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:16,744
Because you are the only one
who can help us

174
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:18,704
to uncover the truth.

175
00:17:52,529 --> 00:17:53,947
You know, buddy,

176
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,408
what you’re doing is dangerous.

177
00:17:57,785 --> 00:17:58,827
We have no choice.

178
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,705
Only Mikoy can be used
to infiltrate the Moraviano family.

179
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:03,290
But how can you be sure

180
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:05,542
that we can trust this Mikoy?

181
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:07,002
How can you be sure

182
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,171
that he hasn’t told his girlfriend yet?

183
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:13,342
We might not get out alive
here in the Czech Republic.

184
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:16,553
And instead of the Czech, we end up dead!

185
00:18:17,679 --> 00:18:19,431
Which begs the question,

186
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:23,185
why hasn’t Mikoy told Chiara about us yet?

187
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:25,187
Of course!

188
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:29,441
If you have a new relationship
with your boyfriend,

189
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,610
would you first ask him,

190
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:36,824
"Hey, sweetheart, is your family
part of a big syndicate?"

191
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:41,120
Because you might get punched
and then break up immediately.

192
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,956
Or maybe deep inside,

193
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:46,166
he is suspicious as well.

194
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,087
Deep inside,

195
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:52,297
he’s not sure about
Chiara’s family either.

196
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,050
I don’t know.

197
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:57,427
Are you thinking what I’m thinking?

198
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:01,348
Fried chicken with IU.

199
00:19:02,015 --> 00:19:03,142
Yes, B1!

200
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:06,353
I'm hungry, and I've been
waiting for a while.

201
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:08,147
No.

202
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:09,148
Then what?

203
00:19:09,231 --> 00:19:10,858
I can’t read everything in your mind.

204
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:13,152
I’m an agent too, buddy.
Just like you, okay?

205
00:19:13,235 --> 00:19:14,111
I’m not a mind reader.

206
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:18,282
Okay.

207
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:23,537
And that is

208
00:19:24,913 --> 00:19:28,750
if the job you give them
is close and important to their life…

209
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:29,877
their loved ones.

210
00:19:36,383 --> 00:19:38,010
What do you mean by that?

211
00:19:38,093 --> 00:19:40,470
Mikoy isn’t just a good family member.

212
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,473
He is the ultimate

213
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:45,517
brother.

214
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:56,612
I want to introduce you to someone.

215
00:19:58,530 --> 00:19:59,364
It’s Angelito.

216
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:03,118
Angelito…

217
00:20:07,956 --> 00:20:12,836
The intelligence of my friend
is not artificial,

218
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:16,006
but pure, old-fashioned hard work.

219
00:20:17,341 --> 00:20:18,717
It means

220
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:21,929
diligence and perseverance-studying
in the library and reading.

221
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:23,639
We don’t really do that.

222
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:25,307
So, bro,

223
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:27,351
take a break from the library today,

224
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:29,144
and come with me.

225
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:33,273
Because we’re going to have
an end-of-semester celebration…

226
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:35,651
tonight.

227
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:39,196
So I can make it up to you for everything
you’ve done for me this sem.

228
00:20:39,863 --> 00:20:42,032
Girls, hop in. Bro, let’s go.

229
00:20:42,115 --> 00:20:43,158
Come on!

230
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:44,701
No more buts!

231
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,036
You deserve to have fun.

232
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:47,246
Let’s go!

233
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:04,263
Hello? I’ve already seen him.

234
00:21:04,346 --> 00:21:05,847
You already know what to do.

235
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:30,247
GOOD MORNING, CHIARA
HAVE A NICE DAY

236
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:32,291
FOR SURE IT WILL BE BECAUSE OF YOU

237
00:21:39,089 --> 00:21:41,675
Bro! Hey! Just relax.

238
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:43,218
This is our celebration.

239
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:45,053
-Our sem is ending.
-Hey!

240
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:45,971
Give it to us!

241
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:47,306
Give it to Angelito!

242
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:50,309
He needs to try it!

243
00:21:50,934 --> 00:21:52,978
Try this one. Have a drink.

244
00:21:55,856 --> 00:21:57,983
Angelito D. Pinagpala!

245
00:22:30,932 --> 00:22:34,436
This is the police! No one escapes!
Get down!

246
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,604
Down!

247
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:39,649
Get down! No one escapes! You! Down!

248
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:04,424
But we have reasons to believe
that Viktor has tapped your phone.

249
00:23:04,508 --> 00:23:06,718
And he is monitoring all your calls.

250
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:11,431
No one can tap this phone.

251
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:13,225
That’s why I can only call you here.

252
00:23:15,102 --> 00:23:16,645
Won’t you stop bothering me?

253
00:23:17,395 --> 00:23:18,480
What else do you need?

254
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:20,440
We need to talk.

255
00:23:21,149 --> 00:23:22,567
There’s something you need to know.

256
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:24,402
Looks like he’s the mastermind!

257
00:23:24,486 --> 00:23:25,987
You stand up!

258
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:27,531
-Put your hands up!
-No, sir--

259
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:29,282
It wasn't me!

260
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:31,201
I am still a student!

261
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:33,745
-Search his pockets!
-No!

262
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:35,080
-What is this?!
-Sir…

263
00:23:35,163 --> 00:23:37,124
-What is this?!
-That’s not mine!

264
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:38,834
Am I not clear enough?

265
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:41,920
I don’t want to be part of your schemes.

266
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:47,968
This also concerns your brother, Angelito.

267
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:53,223
-Not me!
-This one here too!

268
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:55,308
That’s not mine!

269
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:57,144
-Come with us!
-Boss--

270
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:01,898
Let’s meet.

271
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:03,358
I need to talk to you again.

272
00:24:03,441 --> 00:24:04,693
Hey!

273
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:06,862
It was Sianong’s idea to show you this.

274
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:09,948
That your brother was arrested
in a drug den and buy-bust operation.

275
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:11,575
Oh, really?

276
00:24:11,658 --> 00:24:12,534
-What the heck!
-What do you mean no?!

277
00:24:12,617 --> 00:24:13,660
Stop it!

278
00:24:13,743 --> 00:24:15,662
I will tell Chiara the truth.

279
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:19,749
And I will tell her parents
what you’re up to.

280
00:24:20,917 --> 00:24:22,252
You need to know something.

281
00:24:22,335 --> 00:24:24,087
What do I need to know?
